# Rocketship OIDC Configuration Example
# This file shows how to configure Rocketship for external OIDC providers

# =============================================================================
# EXTERNAL OIDC PROVIDER CONFIGURATION (Required for Authentication)
# =============================================================================

# Auth0 Example:
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_ISSUER=https://your-tenant.auth0.com/
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=your-auth0-client-id

# Okta Example (Enterprise):
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_ISSUER=https://your-company.okta.com/oauth2/default
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=your-okta-client-id

# Azure AD Example (Enterprise):
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_ISSUER=https://login.microsoftonline.com/your-tenant-id/v2.0
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=your-azure-client-id

# Google Workspace Example:
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_ISSUER=https://accounts.google.com
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id

# =============================================================================
# ADMIN CONFIGURATION (Required for Initial Setup)
# =============================================================================

# Comma-separated list of admin emails
# These users will automatically become Organization Admins on first login
ROCKETSHIP_ADMIN_EMAILS=admin@your-company.com,devops@your-company.com

# =============================================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION (Required for RBAC)
# =============================================================================

# Auth database configuration (auto-configured in Docker)
# Only needed if running components separately
# ROCKETSHIP_DB_HOST=localhost
# ROCKETSHIP_DB_PORT=5434
# ROCKETSHIP_DB_NAME=auth
# ROCKETSHIP_DB_USER=authuser
# ROCKETSHIP_DB_PASSWORD=authpass

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: CLIENT SECRET (Only needed for confidential clients)
# =============================================================================

# Most OIDC providers support PKCE without client secrets
# Only set this if your provider requires it
# ROCKETSHIP_OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-if-required

# =============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Configure your OIDC provider settings above
# 3. Set your admin emails
# 4. Start your stack: ./.docker/rocketship start
# 5. Login: rocketship auth login
# 6. Create teams: rocketship team create my-team
# 7. Add members: rocketship team add-member my-team user@company.com

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================

# - Never commit .env files with real credentials to version control
# - Use environment-specific .env files for different deployments
# - Admin emails are case-insensitive and whitespace-trimmed
# - PKCE provides security without requiring client secrets